N grstyle.pkg
D  5 Feb 2025
U 3
d 'GRSTYLE': module to customize the overall look of graphs
d 
d  grstyle allows you to customize the overall look of graphs from
d within a do-file without having to fiddle around with external
d scheme files. The advantage of grstyle over manually editing a
d scheme file is that everything needed to reproduce your graphs
d can be included in a single do-file.
d 
d KW: graphics
d KW: scheme files
d KW: custom graphics
d KW: plot
d 
d Requires: Stata version 9.2 and palettes from SSC (q.v.)
d 
d Distribution-Date: 20200919
d 
d Author: Ben Jann, University of Bern
d Support: email jann@@soz.unibe.ch
d 
f g\grstyle.ado
f g\grstyle.hlp
f g\grstyle_set.ado
f g\grstyle_set.hlp
e
S http://fmwww.bc.edu/repec/bocode/i
N iscogen.pkg
D  5 Feb 2025
U 4
d 'ISCOGEN': module to translate ISCO codes
d 
d    iscogen is a tool to translate ISCO codes (International
d Standard Classification of Occupations). Various transformations
d such as  recoding between ISCO-08, ISCO-88, and ISCO-68 or
d generating prestige scores  and occupational classes are
d supported. A command to label ISCO codes is also provided.
d 
d KW:  ISCO-08
d KW: ISCO-88
d KW: ISCO-68
d KW: International Socio-economic Index of Occupational Status ISEI
d KW: Standard International Occupational Prestige Scale SIOPS
d KW: European Socio-economic Classification ESEC
d KW: EGP classes
d KW: OESCH classes
d KW: Magnitude Prestige Scale MPS
d 
d Requires: Stata version 11
d 
d Distribution-Date: 20201117
d 
d Author: Ben Jann, University of Bern
d Support: email jann@@soz.unibe.ch
d 
f i\iscogen.ado
f i\iscogen.sthlp
f i\iscolbl.ado
f i\iscolbl.sthlp
e
S http://fmwww.bc.edu/repec/bocode/e
N entropyetc.pkg
D  5 Feb 2025
U 5
d 'ENTROPYETC': module for entropy and related measures for categories
d 
d  entropyetc treats a single supplied variable, numeric or string,
d as categorical, so that distinct values define distinct
d categories, and calculates the number of distinct categories
d observed, Shannon entropy H, exp H, Simpson's sum of squared
d probabilities R and 1/R.  entropyetc2 is the previous version,
d similar in principle, but different in detail and implementation.
d It is renamed but kept on SSC to allow reproduction of results by
d the previous version. The major issue with this version is that
d it could fail when asked to produce results for very large
d numbers of categories.
d 
d KW: inequality
d KW: diversity
d KW: concentration
d KW: entropy
d KW: Shannon
d KW: Simpson
d KW: Gini
d KW: Herfindahl
d KW: Hirschman
d KW: Turing
d 
d Requires: Stata version 8.2 (entropyyetc), 11.2 (entropyetc2)
d 
d Distribution-Date: 20240621
d 
d Author: Nicholas J. Cox, Durham University
d Support: email N.J.Cox@@durham.ac.uk
d 
f e\entropyetc.ado
f e\entropyetc.sthlp
f e\entropyetc2.ado
f e\entropyetc2.sthlp
e
